Citations
Date:  0/0/1960
Source:  Sheep-O
Author:  MILLS
Vol / Page:  122
Edition:
Quote:  In those days .. a shearer had to shear cleanly, or have many of his sheep heavily marked in the count-out pens and excluded from his tally. Inevitably the boss stood to benefit from such a one-sided bargain, hence the term, raddle money.
